First Read: 29-Jan-26
SB231 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Legislature; to amend Section 29-4-4,
5 Code of Alabama 1975, to provide security for the Legislature
6 in the new Alabama State House, legislative parking deck, and
7 park adjacent to the new Alabama State House and at official
8 legislative events held off-site; to create the crime of
9 unlawful use of unmanned aircraft systems within the Capitol
10 complex; to provide for penalties; to exempt certain persons
11 from the crime of unlawful use of unmanned aircraft systems
12 within the Capitol complex; and to authorize the Alabama State
13 Law Enforcement Agency to take certain actions.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. Section 29-4-4, Code of Alabama 1975, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 "§29-4-4
18 (a) Unless provided otherwise by law or applicable
19 legislative rule or policy, security personnel employed by the
20 House of Representatives and the Senate shall be responsible
21 for the security of all of the following:
22 (1) The third, fourth, fifth, sixth, seventh, and
23 eighth floors of the Alabama State House located at 11 South
24 Union Street, such other areas within the Alabama State House
25 as which are occupied or used by the Legislature, and such
26 additional areas outside the Alabama State House in accordance
27 with Section 29-1-19.
28 (2) The new Alabama State House, as coordinated by the
