29 Secretary of the Legislative Council, the Secretary of the
30 Senate, and the Clerk of the House of Representatives.
31 (3) The legislative parking deck and park located
32 between South Union Street and the new Alabama State House.
33 (4) During any official legislative event, as
34 designated by the President Pro Tempore of the Senate and
35 Speaker of the House of Representatives in coordination with
36 the Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency, held in the State of
37 Alabama away from the Capitol complex.
38 (b) The security officers employed under this chapter
39 shall have the powers of peace officers in this state and may
40 exercise those powers only in the areas designated in
41 subsection (a).
42 (c) The Alabama State Law Enforcement Agency, in
43 coordination with the Legislative Council, shall be
44 responsible for the security of the perimeter and points of
45 entry to the Alabama State House and new Alabama State House
46 as prescribed by the Legislative Council.
47 (d)(1) Every department, agency, and bureau of the
48 State of Alabama shall assist in any manner requested by the
49 Legislature in assuring the security of the areas of the
50 Alabama State House designated in subsection (a).
51 (2) Subsection (c) shall apply to any convening of the
52 Legislature outside of the Capitol or away from the Alabama
53 State House in accordance with Sections 48 or 48.01 of the
54 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, or other applicable law.
55 (e) For purposes of this section, "new Alabama State
56 House" means the building bounded by Pelham Street, South
